{"id":"core-demo","name":"Vehicle Forge Demo Vehicles","version":"1.0","publisher":"Glassforge Games Ltd.","description":"3 vehicles \u2014 Sample builds demonstrating the Vehicle Forge across three genres: civilian ground, military armour, and modern aviation.","weapons":[],"mods":[],"specials":[],"vehicles":[{"name":"Mid-Size Sedan","size":4,"loco":"wheeled","desc":"Four doors, air bags, reasonable legroom. Your Camrys, Accords, and fleet rental staples.","notes":"Your Camrys, Accords, Passats, and fleet rental staples. She carries more passengers and gear than the compact, handles roughly the same, and blends into traffic just as easily. Also covers unmarked police cars, taxi cabs, and the anonymous saloon your players steal when they need to move without attracting attention. The world's most forgettable getaway car.","toughLevel":0,"armourLevel":0,"speedLevel":1,"handlingLevel":0,"mods":{},"weapons":[],"specials":["enclosed","cargo_bay"],"customSpecial":"","passengers":4,"mphOverride":120},{"name":"WW2 Medium Tank (Allied)","size":8,"loco":"tracked","desc":"The workhorse Allied tank. Shermans, Cromwells, and their equivalents \u2014 reliable, mass-produced, outgunned by late-war heavies.","notes":"The M4 Sherman and its variants \u2014 the M4A1 with cast hull, the M4A3E8 'Easy Eight' with improved suspension, the Firefly with its 17-pounder gun. Also covers Cromwells, Crusaders, and other mid-war Allied designs. She wasn't the best tank of the war \u2014 late-war German armour outgunned her routinely \u2014 but there were always more of them. Use her as the reliable, available option that wins through numbers and logistics rather than individual superiority. Heavy Armor, Tracked.","armourLevel":2,"speedLevel":0,"handlingLevel":0,"mods":{},"weapons":[{"weaponId":"tank_gun_75mm","mount":"turret","linked":0},{"weaponId":"mmg","mount":"fixed","linked":0},{"weaponId":"hmg","mount":"pintle","linked":0}],"specials":["heavy_armor","enclosed"],"customSpecial":"","mphOverride":30},{"name":"Modern Air Superiority Fighter","size":9,"loco":"jet","desc":"Twin-engine, Mach 2.5, designed to own the sky. Eagles, Flankers, Typhoons, and Rafales.","notes":"F-15 Eagles, F-22 Raptors, Eurofighter Typhoons, Dassault Rafales, Saab Gripens, and their equivalents. Twin-engine, Mach 2+ capable, designed to own the sky from visual range to beyond-visual-range. The F-15 has never been shot down in air-to-air combat. The F-22 was built to ensure that record continues. She's the thing your players hear about but never want to see on the wrong side. Night Vision.","toughLevel":0,"armourLevel":-1,"speedLevel":3,"handlingLevel":3,"mods":{},"weapons":[{"weaponId":"cannon_20mm","mount":"fixed","linked":0},{"weaponId":"sidewinder","mount":"fixed","linked":0},{"weaponId":"sparrow","mount":"fixed","linked":0}],"specials":["enclosed","night_ops"],"customSpecial":"","crewLevel":-4,"mphOverride":1875}]}